Draft migration of vLLM's FlashInfer autotune warmup onto flashinfer.autotune_v2()
(managed per-entry store, PR flashinfer-ai/flashinfer#3861, RFC #3920).

What this deletes: vLLM's own cache hashing, atomic-write, leader-broadcast and
load_configs plumbing (flashinfer_autotune_cache.py entirely, ~56 lines, plus
~40 lines of kernel_warmup.py).  What vLLM keeps: deciding WHEN to warm up and
the barrier around it.

Behavior changes (all improvements over status quo):
- multi-rank deployments get PERSISTENT tuning results again (currently
  disabled entirely for world_size > 1 since vllm#43119); all ranks tune
  concurrently into one shared store — per-entry atomic publish makes this
  safe, and restarts reuse it.
- single-node consistency after restart: all ranks read the same store.
  In-session cross-rank divergence is unchanged vs today's multi-rank path;
  the flashinfer-side finalize step (tune -> barrier -> reload, tracked in
  flashinfer#3186/#3187) removes it once available.
- VLLM_FLASHINFER_AUTOTUNE_CACHE_DIR maps onto cache_root= (placement only;
  environment isolation is flashinfer's job now).

